  %h1 Block tags
%section
  %pre
    %code.html
      &lt;em&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;span&gt; &lt;a&gt; &lt;img&gt;
  %p
    These are line tags (they do not cause a line break&nbsp;below).
%section
  %pre
    %code.html
      &lt;p&gt; &lt;h1&gt; &lt;h2&gt; &lt;h3&gt; &lt;h4&gt; â€¦
  %p
    These are block tags (they cause a line break), but they are aimed to contain
    text strings (not other block&nbsp;tags).

%section
  %pre
    %code.html
      &lt;div&gt;
  %p
    This block tag is used to create structures, blocks and groups of&nbsp;blocks.

%section
  %pre
    %code.html
      :preserve
        <div class="header">
          <h1>Heading</h1>
          <p>Content</p>
        </div>
  %p
    We can group contents into a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> tag and apply styles with a&nbsp;class.

%section
  %pre
    %code.html
      :preserve
        <div class="header">
          <h1>Heading</h1>
          <p>Content</p>
          <div class="highlight">
            <p>Highlighted text</p>
            <p>Highlighted text</p>
          </div>
        </div>
  %p
    The <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> tags can be grouped into each other to create
    more complex&nbsp;structures.
